This paper deals with a scheduling problem involving energy consumption and processing volumes, which suggests it could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS) or information theory (cs.IT). Additionally, the problem involves optimization and minimizing energy consumption, which could also place it in the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the NP-hardness of the problem, which could make it relevant to the category of performance analysis (cs.PF).
